speech.p:
Motion made, and Question proposed,
That for the purposes of any Act resulting from the Education Reform Bill, it is expedient to authorise—
(1)the payment out of money provided by Parliament of any sums required by the Secretary of State—


(a) for making grants to the governing body of a grant-maintained school;

(b) in respect of expenses incurred in connection with the proposed acquisition in the case of any school, of grant-maintained status;

(c)for making payments in respect of the establishing, maintaining or carrying on of any city technology college;

(d)for making grants to the following bodies established by the Act, namely, the Universities Funding Council, the Polytechnics and Colleges Funding Council and the Education Assets Board;

(e)for defraying the expenses of the following bodies established by the Act, namely the National Curriculum Council, the Curriculum Council for Wales and the School Examinations and Assessment Council;

(f)in connection with the commissioning by the Secretary of State of work for facilitating the discharge, in relation to Wales, of his functions in respect of the National Curriculum;

(g)for paying remuneration to, and defraying the expenses of, the University Commissioners appointed under the Act; and

(h)in respect of any administrative expenses incurred by the Secretary of State under the Act;
(2) any increase attributable to the Act in the sums payable under any other Act out of money so provided; and
(3) the payment of sums into the Consolidation Fund.— [Mrs. Rumbold.]

Resolved,
That, for the purposes of any Act resulting from the Education Reform Bill, it is expedient to authorize—
(1) the payment out of money provided by Parliament of any sums required by the Secretary of State—


(a) for making grants to the governing body of a grant-maintained school;

(b) in respect of expenses incurred in connection with the proposed acquisition, in the case of any school, of grant-maintained status;

(c) for making payments in respect of the establishing, maintaining or carrying on of any city technology college;

(d) for making grants to the following bodies established by the Act, namely, the Universities Funding Council, the Polytechnics and Colleges Funding Council and the Education Assets Board;

(e) for defraying the expenses of the following bodies established by the Act, namely, the National Curriculum Council, the Curriculum Council for Wales and the School Examinations and Assessment Council;

(f) in connection with the commissioning by the Secretary of State of work for facilitating the discharge, in relation to Wales, of his functions in respect of the National Curriculum;

(g) for paying remuneration to, and defraying the expenses of, the University Commissioners appointed under the Act; and

(h) in respect of any administrative expenses incurred by the Secretary of State under the Act.
(2) any increase attributable to the Act in the sums payable under any other Act out of money so provided; and
(3) the payment of sums into the Consolidated Fund.
